  "body": "Forked from https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/42736#issuecomment-285268573. \r\n\r\nCurrently, kuberuntime garbage collection can't distinguish just-created sandboxes from failed sandboxes. Especially when the time from sandbox creation to ready is longer than GC's minAge. In such cases, those sandboxes may be garbage collected early before they are ready.\r\n\r\nSome ideas of solving this problem:\r\n\r\n- runtime (e.g. dockershim) filter out those created-but-not-ready sandboxes from sandbox list\r\n- introduce another sandbox state CREATED in CRI\r\n\r\ncc @yujuhong @kubernetes/sig-node-bugs ",
